<p>I dig it. </p>

<p>In response to the question about reStructuredText, I would just point out the contrast between these two documents:  </p>

<ul>
<li><a href="http://docutils.sourceforge.net/docs/rst/quickstart.txt">reStructuredText primer in reStructuredText format</a>  </li>
<li><a href="../2002/html2text/index.html?url=http:%252F%252Fdocutils.sourceforge.net%252Fdocs%252Frst%252Fquickstart.html">reStructuredText primer in Markdown format</a> (via html2text)</li>
</ul>

<p>The Markdown format is a lot easier to read, and probably a lot easier to write.  The HTML output from passing that html2text text back through Markdown is a little different than the original HTML document, but I don&#8217;t think it would be difficult to get it back to nearly the same result.  The point is the difference between producing a piece of writing and creating an HTML document.  Having to do the first by also doing the second is tedious.</p>

<p>I also dig that Markdown.pl works as a blosxom plugin out of the box. (Btw, if you use the writeback plugin, I have a 1 line diff for adding Markdown support to user writebacks <a href="http://greg.vario.us/software/writeback.patch">here</a>.)</p>

